{ The following model games are dedicated to the line } 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nd2 e6 5. Nb3 { This positional system is designed to restrict Black's counterplay based on the advance ...c6-c5. In the long term, White will obviously try to develop his typical kingside play. Against this system, I suggest the rare } 5... a6 { In the annotations to the model games, you will see why it's so important to take the b5-square under control before going for ... c6-c5. The theory is not important at all in this line. What you need is a good understanding of the typical structures. } *
