1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nf3 e6 5. Be2 Nd7 6. O-O a5 7. a4 f6 8. Be3 {White develops the bishop to a stable square. The main drawback of this approach is that after ...fxe5 dxe5, Black has the resource of ...Bc5.} fxe5 9. dxe5 {In my opinion, this recapture is slightly less precise in view of Black's next move.} ({A bit better would have been} 9. Nxe5 {White not only prevents the exchange of the dark-squared bishops but is also ready to start advancing the kingside pawns. The structure arising after} Bd6 10. f4 Ne7 11. Nd2 O-O {is quite double-edged. Black's counterplay is based on the semi-open f-file and the weakened light squares in the centre. White's most aggressive approach to the position is} 12. g4 Bg6 {[%cal Gd6c7,Gd7e5] getting ready for ...Bc7 followed by ...Nxe5.} 13. h4 h5 14. gxh5 Nf5 15. Bf2 Be8 $13 {Black has sufficient counterplay in this complex position.}) 9... Bc5 10. Bxc5 {The most logical continuation. White is planning to proceed with Nd4 followed by the advance of the kingside pawns.} ({The immediate} 10. Nd4 {will be met by} Bxd4 $1 {Again, it's very typical for the Advanced Caro-Kann that Black gives up this bishop to keep the one on f5, which is usually the more important piece.} 11. Bxd4 Ne7 {As we know, with this piece configuration, Black tries to apply the so-called light square strategy. A possible line would be} 12. f4 O-O 13. Nd2 b6 14. Be3 Nc5 15. Nf3 h6 16. Nd4 Be4 $13 {with enough counterplay.}) 10... Nxc5 11. Nd4 Ne7 12. Bh5+ {Before proceeding with the strategy based on g2-g4, White wants to provoke the advance ...g7-g6.} ({Better would have been} 12. Qd2 $5 O-O 13. Qe3 {questioning the c5-knight. In this case, a possible line would have been} Na6 14. Na3 (14. g4 c5 $13) 14... Nc7 15. c3 Be4 16. Qd2 $1 Nf5 17. Nxf5 Bxf5 18. Nc2 {With some initiative for White in a complex position.}) 12... g6 13. Be2 Qb6 14. g4 $2 {It turns out that this natural move does not work tactically.} ({White could have played} 14. Ra3 h5 $1 15. Qc1 Bg4 16. Nd2 Nf5 $13 {with an unclear position.}) 14... Be4 $36 {After this move, Black overtakes the initiative. Even though the remaining part of the game is left without comments, you can enjoy the dynamic resources of Black's position.} 15. Nc3 h5 16. f3 O-O-O 17. fxe4 dxe4 18. Qd2 hxg4 19. Bxg4 Nf5 20. Bxf5 gxf5 21. Nce2 Nd7 22. Ra3 Nxe5 23. Rb3 Qc5 24. Qc3 Nc4 25. Kh1 e3 26. Nf3 e5 27. Nxe5 Qd5+ 28. Nf3 Nd2 29. Qg7 c5 30. Rd3 Nxf3 31. Qg2 Rxh2+ 32. Qxh2 Nd4+ 33. Kg1 Nxe2+ 34. Qxe2 Rg8+ 35. Kh2 Qe5+ 36. Kh1 Qe4+ 0-1

