1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bd3 Bxd3 6. Qxd3 Qa5+ $1 7. Nc3 (7. c3 Qa6 $1 (7... e6 8. a4 $5 Qa6 9. Qd1 {transposes to 8.Qd1 and the minor alternative 8....e6}) 8. Qd1 (8. Qf3 {may lead to lively positions, for example} e6 9. b4 $5 (9. a4 c5 10. Na3 $2 Qxa4 $17) 9... Qa4 $1 10. Ne2 (10. Bg5 {is also answered with the intended} a5 $13) 10... a5 11. bxa5 Rxa5 12. O-O Nd7 ({premature is} 12... Qc2 {, as in Mareco - Cori, Mexican op, 2021, because of} 13. a4 $36) 13. Nd2 (13. Bg5 Be7 14. Rc1 Bxg5 15. hxg5 Ne7 $13) 13... b5 14. Nb3 Ra7 15. Nf4 {Here Black can obtain decent play by choosing one of the alternatives} g6 ({or} 15... Ne7 $5 16. Nxh5 $14 Nxe5 $1 17. Qe2 Nd7 18. Re1 Qc4 19. Qf3 e5 $13) 16. Nd3 Nh6 (16... Ba3 $5 17. Bxa3 Qxa3 18. Nbc5 Nxc5 19. Nxc5 Ne7 $13 {[%cal Ge7f5]}) 17. Nb2 Qa3 18. c4 Nf5 $1 (18... bxc4 19. Nxc4 Qa4 {J. Burke - J. Liang, Washington, 2022} 20. Bxh6 dxc4 21. Bxf8 $14) 19. cxb5 cxb5 $13) 8... c5 $1 {A well-timed counterstrike:} ({As mentioned, the natural} 8... e6 {is a bit slow because of} 9. a4 c5 10. Na3 $1 cxd4 (10... c4 $6 11. b3 $1 Nd7 12. bxc4 Bxa3 13. Bxa3 Qxc4 14. Ne2 $16 {Vokhidov - Samunenkov, Titled Tuesday 31st May, 2022}) 11. Nb5 Qb6 12. Nxd4 Nc6 13. Ngf3 $36) 9. Ne2 (9. a4 {is less effective here in the view of} cxd4 10. cxd4 e6 11. Nc3 Nc6 {Black has already fixed the central structure and should not be afraid of the jump to the b5-square any longer, e.g.} 12. Nf3 (12. Nb5 Qb6 $15) 12... Bb4 $13) 9... e6 10. Nd2 cxd4 11. cxd4 Nh6 {with a fine version of the French -} 12. Nf3 Nf5 13. Bg5 (13. O-O Be7 $11) 13... Qa5+ $1 14. Kf1 Nc6 15. g3 Be7 $11) 7... e6 8. Bg5 {The pet move order of Paravyan.} (8. Nf3 Qa6 $1 9. Qd1 Bb4 10. Bd2 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Nd7 12. b4 Ne7 $13 {is absolutely fine for Black, Garau - Duchardt, FRA-ch email, 2021.}) 8... c5 $1 {A concrete and logical reaction.} ({Its preparation by means of} 8... Ne7 9. Nge2 (9. Nf3 $5) 9... Nd7 10. O-O a6 {is time-consuming and White has every reason to strike with} 11. b4 $1 Qc7 12. Nf4 $1 ({an improvement upon} 12. Ng3 f6 13. exf6 gxf6 $13 {Paravyan - Eljanov, Titled Tuesday 31st May, 2022}) 12... Nf5 13. Nd1 Be7 14. Bxe7 Nxe7 15. Ne3 $36 {and better prospects on both wings.}) 9. Qb5+ ({Nothing special is} 9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. Nf3 Nh6 $13) 9... Qxb5 10. Nxb5 Kd7 $1 ({Black should better refrain from misplacing his knight -} 10... Na6 {as in dropstoneDP - eljanov Live Chess Chess.com, 2022, to which} 11. Nf3 cxd4 12. Nfxd4 $14 {is emphasizing on a problem with the a7-pawn as well.}) 11. c4 a6 12. Nc3 cxd4 13. Na4 Ra7 $1 14. Rc1 $1 ({But not} 14. cxd5 $2 b5 $1 {, when Na4 is in trouble -} 15. dxe6+ Kxe6 $17) 14... dxc4 15. Nb6+ Kc7 (15... Ke8 $5 {is fully playable, White, if he wishes so, can force a repetition by} 16. Nc8 Ra8 $11) 16. Nxc4 Nc6 17. Nf3 Nh6 18. Ke2 $140 a5 $5 19. Bxh6 gxh6 20. Rhd1 Bc5 $13 *

