{ In positions with rooks on the board, everything changes. Now, the position is no longer better for White since he cannot put the queenside majority into motion. Black is ready to maneuver the king to d6. A possible line would be } 1. Rd1 Kf8 2. Bc2 Ke7 3. Re1 Kd6 4. f4 b5 $11 { This standard move always comes into consideration. White's queenside majority is completely ineffective. The position is equal. } *
