1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Nxf6+ exf6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qc2 Re8+ 9. Ne2 h5 10. O-O h4 11. h3 Nd7 12. Bf4 Nf8 13. Bxd6 Qxd6 14. Qd2 Ng6 15. Rfe1 Be6 {Black has managed to comfortably develop his pieces. Most probably, his next move is going to be ...Rad8 after which White should always reckon with the advance ...c6-c5. Whenever the white knight leaves the e2-square, Black can consider ...Nf4. Another thematic idea in such positions is ...Ne7 followed by ...Bf5. The exchange of the light-squared bishops is quite favourable for Black. In the game, White decided to force a transition into an endgame by means of} 16. Bxg6 fxg6 17. Qf4 {Strategically speaking, this decision is quite dubious since in the endgame arising after} Qxf4 18. Nxf4 Bf7 {The bishop is superior to the knight. As mentioned earlier in this lecture, the knight lacks outposts in this pawn structure. Black can start gaining space on both wings while White's queenside majority is completely ineffective. The game continued} 19. a3 g5 20. Nd3 Bc4 21. Nc5 b6 22. Ne4 Rad8 23. f3 Kf7 $15 {Black has an obvious advantage. Later on, he will proceed with ...Kg6 followed by ...f6-f5. At the same time, White does not have any constructive ideas. Since this is just an online blitz game, I leave the remaining moves without annotations.} 24. Kf2 Kg6 25. Nd2 Be6 26. Re2 Bf7 27. Rae1 Rxe2+ 28. Rxe2 Rd7 29. Ke1 f5 30. Kf2 Kf6 31. Ke1 Be6 32. Re5 c5 33. Re3 cxd4 34. cxd4 Rxd4 35. Rc3 g4 36. Rc7 Rd7 37. Rc6 gxh3 38. gxh3 g5 39. Ke2 Re7 40. Ke3 Kf7 41. Kf2 Rd7 42. Nf1 f4 43. Kg2 Rd3 44. Rc7+ Kf6 45. Rxa7 Rb3 46. Rc7 Rxb2+ 47. Kg1 Bxh3 48. Nh2 Be6 49. Rc6 Ke5 50. Rc3 Rb3 51. Rc6 Rxa3 52. Rxb6 h3 53. Rb5+ Kf6 54. Rc5 Ra1+ 55. Kf2 Rh1 56. Ng4+ Bxg4 57. fxg4 Rh2+ 58. Kf3 Rg2 59. Rc6+ Ke7 60. Rh6 Rg3+ 61. Ke4 Kf7 62. Kf5 f3 63. Kxg5 Ke7 64. Rh7+ Ke6 65. Kf4 f2 66. Kxg3 f1=Q 67. Rxh3 Kf6 68. Rh5 Qe2 69. Rf5+ Kg6 70. Kf4 Qf2+ 71. Ke4 Qg3 72. Rf4 Kg5 73. Rf8 Qxg4+ 74. Ke5 Qe2+ 75. Kd5 Qd3+ 76. Ke6 Qc4+ 77. Ke7 Qc5+ 78. Ke8 Qe5+ 79. Kd8 Qd6+ 80. Ke8 Qc7 0-1

